definition: to hook/to sew/to crochet/hook/check mark or tick/window catch

sentences.english: The profile of the old warrior was characterized by a strong jaw and an aquiline nose.
sentences.chinese: 老戰士側面像的特徵是一個堅硬的下巴和一個鷹鉤鼻。

sentences.english: He was born a hooked nose.
But look at her nose. It’s a little bit too long and hooked at the end.
sentences.chinese: 可瞧她的鼻子，是稍有點長的鷹鉤鼻。

sentences.english: He had a aquiline nose and deep-set brown eyes.
sentences.chinese: 他擁有鷹鉤鼻和深邃的棕色眼睛。

sentences.english: You'll have a very natural Roman nose then.
sentences.chinese: 到時你就會有一個很自然的鷹鉤鼻。

sentences.english: Bozo was a small, dark, hook-nosed man, with curly hair growing low on his head.
sentences.chinese: 博佐是個小個子，膚色黑，鷹鉤鼻子，一頭捲髮挺長。

sentences.english: The hook-nosed man has been wandering around for some time since noon.
sentences.chinese: 從中午起，那個長着鷹鉤鼻子的男人就一直四處徘徊。

sentences.english: I wish I had a Roman nose.
sentences.chinese: 我希望我有一個鷹鉤鼻。

sentences.english: A. He am born a hooked nose.
He has got an oval face and a booked nose.
sentences.chinese: 他有一張橢圓形臉和一個鷹鉤鼻。
